<TITLE> Stock market sees volatility, ends flat </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Dec 13 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka stocks ended mostly steady in a market that saw wild fluctuation of prices. Benchmark index, the DGEN, rose steeply on the opening bell and remained more or less stable with small fluctuations across the morning-to-mid session before falling in the last hour. It edged up 0.77 points or .01 percent, to close at 4438.50. The broader DSI, or all share price index, ended at 3685.13, shedding 2.98 points or 0.08 percent. The day's trading caused more than 65 percent of traded scrips to fall, with losers outnumbering gainers by 155 to 76 and three holding steady. The market driver, banks, continued their rally though at a slower pace compared to the previous day. The sector gained 1.5 percent on an average compared with Thursday's 3.3 percent. Out of the 24 traded issues of banks, five rose over 2 percent. Meanwhile, all the non-bank financial institutions lost excepting IDLC, Uttara Finance and Bay Leasing & Investments. Most of the insurers fell while mutual funds witnessed mixed trend. Oil Company shares plunged but power and energy issues had a good day. The daily turnover of the country's prime bourse fell to Tk 10.20 billion from the previous session's Tk 11.44 billion. AB Bank made as the turnover leader with shares worth Tk 683.732 million traded followed by Beximco, Shahjalal Islami Bank, NCC Bank and Bex Tex. Meanwhile, the Chittagong Stock Exchange ended up backed by gains in banks, leasing & finance organisations and pharmaceutical companies. The benchmark Selective Categories Index or the CSCX ended at 8362.45, up by 48.41 points or 0.58 percent. AB Bank topped the turnover list with shares of Tk 67.28 million changing hands followed by Beximco, Grameenphone, Shahjalal Islami Bank and Bex Tex. 
